[1] Cholera - Nigeria
Date: Fri, 12 Nov 2004
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Xinhuanet.com [edited]
<http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2004-11/12/content_2210463.htm>

Cholera epidemic kills 50 in southwest Nigeria
-----------------------------------------------
At least 50 people have been killed and over 300 others still critically
ill in hospitals following a cholera epidemic in southwest Nigeria,
according to the Punch newspaper Fri, 12 Nov 2004.
Already, residents have in hundreds started fleeing Owan West local
government area in northwestern Edo state where the cholera epidemic
occurred, raising fears that such mass movement may cause a spread of the
waterborne disease in the neighboring towns.
Godwin Ovbiagele, health commissioner of the state, has dispatched 20
additional doctors and other medical personnel and materials to the
affected area. He also ordered that all patients should be treated free of
charge so that the disease would not spread further.
The outbreak of the deadly disease was first noticed a week earlier, and
it grew into epidemic proportions when the first victims refused to go to
the hospital for treatment, the report said. The epidemic might have been
caused by consumption of contaminated water, it added.
A similar cholera epidemic occurred in the same area in 1974 when hundreds
of people died.
