[2] Cholera - Senegal
Date: 12 Nov 2004
From: Marianne Hopp <mjh12@yahoo.com>
Source: WHO CSR update [edited]
<http://www.who.int/csr/don/2004_11_12/en/>

Cholera in Senegal - update
-----------------------------
As of 10 Nov 2004, WHO has received reports from the Ministry of Health of
a total number of 861 cases and 6 deaths in Dakar. In Dakar the incidence
of the disease appears to be decreasing.
In addition to implementing control measures, including health education,
case management and surveillance and monitoring in the affected areas, the
National Outbreak Management Committee has undertaken social mobilization
activities and decontamination of unsanitary areas. Senior government
officials have been active in disseminating health education and hygiene
messages in the mass media.
For more information
- WHO cholera publications
<http://www.who.int/topics/cholera/en/>
- Cholera in Senegal
<http://www.who.int/csr/don/2004_11_02/en/>
